Title: Lasko Digital Ceramic Heater 1500 Watts CC13700 * used *
Reviews: ['My Lasko CC13700 was manufactured Feb 2019 Purchased 11/11/19 from a local store. This was made in China where forced labor is documented but Laskoâ€™s Social Responsibility statement addresses that issue: â€œLasko and its affiliates will not work with any suppliers that engage in human trafficking and/or slavery.â€ The CC13700 seemed like it had an unusually strong odor new out of the box while it was heating. The heat was great but using it with the odor in the living area brought some unpleasant upper respiratory irritation and potential health issues that go along with that. After it aired out during the first year, the odor was not as noticeable in a well-ventilated area. At the end of the second season, it began to shut off immediately after turning on. It was under warranty so I sent an email to customer service and got a helpful reply the same evening. The suggestion of blowing air into the unit from the outside was a temporary fix for a few months but the heater eventually stopped blowing heat again so I submitted a warranty request. Due to the Lasko heater breakdown, I bought a new baseboard-style heater (without the chemical odor) before getting the replacement. Lasko Consumer Services stood behind the 3 year warranty. CC13700 was on back order and not available so they offered a different model. I did not have to pay return shipping and received a replacement fan heater within 15 days. Itâ€™s great to have to have a new Lasko fan heater, but it reintroduces the same indoor air pollution so Iâ€™m using this one away from the bedroom and main living areas to give it a year to air out. Regarding the CC13700 magnetic field, I checked it with a Triaxial ELF Magnetic Field Meter and found that the magnetic field from the motor was almost 48â€ in all directions, so I kept that in mind to maintain some distance while the heater was in use. The closed design with easy-vacuum filter is a nice innovation compared with open design fan heaters. Weekly filter vacuuming was essential to keep the plastic case cool and AC plug prongs from getting too hot in the outlet. I wish I could give the CC13700 more than 2 stars because it was excellent at putting out heat but apparently it wasnâ€™t built to last. I think a heater should work for 5 years to earn a 5 star rating but this stopped working in less than 2 years. Fortunately there was a 3 year warranty and Lasko handled the warranty replacement very well (but the replacement heater deserves separate review because it is a different product and model number.) If the CC13700 could be repaired and used again, I would be open to editing the review with a higher rating because it was great before it stopped working. This was powerful and it produced instant hot air: I set Automatic Temperature Control about 15 degrees lower than expected to get the desired level of heat. (CC13700 digital temperature at the floor reads lower than other thermometers that I have and since heat rises, it might take several hours to raise floor temperature one degree in a small room, even with the door shut, while temperature 5 feet above the heater may be 10-20 degrees higher than what is shown on the display.) At first I didnâ€™t like the CC13700 because it has an ergonomic design flaw that took awhile to get used to, in which placing the fingers under the carry handle makes it feel like it might be easy to tip over or drop. Regarding the digital controls: Pressing the red On button starts the heater on Hi setting. The 2 left buttons activate Automatic Temperature Control with digital setting range from 39F-90F (which must be set with the heater turned on and running). After selecting temperature, the DIGITAL DISPLAY FLASHES SEVERAL TIMES. IT IS NOT NECESSARY TO DO ANYTHING ELSE AT THAT POINT. Wait for the display to return to indicate the current room temperature and the Automatic Temperature Control should be set.  Automatic Temperature Control seems to have 3 degree temperature window which raises the temperature 2 degrees above the thermostat setting and drops one degree below before resuming operation. AC power interruption resets digital features to factory default. Pressing the middle timer button reveals 9 settings to set the timer between 1-8 hours or continuous. Adjustable louver control for directional heat is a nice feature made possible by the closed design.', 'Ordered 2 heaters,Wanted to send them back because they were way  to small,but I deceived to try them and boy do they heat up,I got so worm I had to kick off the blankets in the middle of the night.For such a small heater they generate a lot of heat.', 'High temp trips my 20 amp breaker. works fine on low', 'heat my bathroom very well love it', 'This product heats the interior of a 36 foot Avion 5th wheel RV when the outside temperature is >30 degrees F. It is safe and reliable.', 'Good', 'I bought this heater to help maintain a constant temperature for my birds. Before this one I tried 3 other kinds. This one is great and does exactly what it says!', "This item DOES NOT have a safety shut off, if it tips over. I've tested it, laying it down on the front or back DOES NOT shut it off. I thought a shut off was required of all heaters.", 'great product and great price']

Title: Lasko 101 White My Heat Personal Ceramic Heater New Open Box
Reviews: ["Have had both Eden Pure and Duraflame models used in my home. When comparing to the Dr. Infared DR-968, the most notable option that it lacks over the above mentioned is that you can not set run time for say, 3 hours or longer. This being a feature I believe, would make the DR-968 better. Honestly can't say how it will hold up as I've just recently purchased it. So far, it's doing the job at keeping my bedroom comfortable. It is being used as supplemental heat which helps keep my furnace from running non stop. It's size is smaller than the other two mentioned which is nice. I'm hopeful that it will provide long term use before heating elements give out as was the case with the other two models. Hope this review is of use to you.", 'using it to heat a small 5 x 5 entrance hall it heats it very good without using a lotof power', 'As others have said, it is small. But, at 200 watts, it was to be expected. It puts off enough heat to keep your legs warm under a desk, for example but would not heat an open area sufficiently. I purchased for my wife to use under her desk, and she likes it.', "Very nice little electric heater, very small, quiet, only uses 200 watts, perfect for heating a small waiting room with outside walls and windows when it's 30s and up outside. Excellent value.", 'I bought this heater to heat a very small space, and I am surprised at how much heat it puts out.Temperatures here often reach well below zero, and I wanted a little heat in a room farthest from my wood stove.I like the construction as it seems to be quite sturdy.I also like the fan which circulates air out of the heater. I thought it was radiant heat only, but the fan inside moves the heat far beyond the heater.I do wish it had a control allowing for running at a lower power.  There is one switch only, for off and on. I wish it was thermostatically controlled, but for the price (under 20 dollars), it seems to be a good product.', "Perfect heat for my home office. Keeps the chill off and I don't have to heat the whole house to keep the room warm. A+ heater", ' My dog says thank you for keeping him warm this winter. ', "I use it for the bathroom, plug it in just before I enter the tub & the temp is just right when I exit.It doesn't blow the circuit like other heaters. It is light & portable.  It is safe. Title: Vornado VH203 Personal Heater & Gold-Compact Cool Touch Electric 750w
Reviews: ["This item is functional as a fan but the heater settings are not very hot.  The only real advantage of this item is that the lower electricity usage keeps the cord & electric plug from becoming dangerously hot and melting your electric outlet (like with other heaters  1000W).  Other than that I can't really say much else about this item.  Since my bed area is just an open space in the men's dorm of my recuperative care shelter I have no idea if these machines can really circulate the air in a small enclosedspace.  I am glad to have two of them though because my bed is right under a vent duct in the ceiling and with the AC over functioning I get a lot of cold air blowing on me at all hours.  But I'm basically sleeping with the heaters in my bed on high because of the weaker heat settings.  Caveat empetor.", 'Great personal heater, fairly quiet (white noise, basically), perfect for a small space like on an office desk or while sitting on the sofa. Title: Handy Heater | Plug-In Personal Heater | Compact Design | Quick and Easy
Reviews: ['I purchased this heater for a very specific purpose. I needed a small heater to dry out a wood window sill for a window located in a bathroom shower (long story). This heater satisfied all of my requirements which included: small enough to fit in the space between the storm window and double hung window, generate enough heat to dry the space without over heating, have a thermostat, and operate continuously for a prolonged period of time. I have not had any problems operating this unit on a heavy duty extension cord (not recommended in instructions). This unit will automatically turn on and off as it reaches the temperature you set for the unit. It produces just enough heat to satisfy my need. Criticisms regarding the 12 hour time limit can be resolved by plugging this unit into a timer. When the power is shut off and then back on, the unit will run again for 12 hours intervals solving the problem of having to be present to restart the unit. This unit must be suspended to prevent blockage of the air intake located on the bottom of the heater.', "Quality feels good, not cheap. Plug rotation feature is secure and not wobbly or junky at all. Heater pulls 297 watts when running, but pulls ~750 watts for about 30 seconds when you turn it on from cold. This is a powerful little heater, you would not want to put your hand directly in front of it for very long. Definitely enough to heat a very small space like a car, or heat up a small room which isn't quite warm enough. Has a thermostat which works well. The heater will run the fan for a bit and cycle down just as it should. It has a red LED which always stays on and give the impression of a hot surface so that you don't forget that the grill could still be hot.The heater sucks air in from the bottom where the fan is.Honestly, this thing has better construction and features than most space heaters I've owned.Cannot yet speak to reliability but based on the good circuit design it should last quite a long time.", 'We have an L shaped bath room and the  baseboard heater is on the long side. On cold days the far corner of the short side gets cold.  This gadget is perfect, set temperature and  shave in comfort. easy to use, takes no space. I saved about  $1200 by not adding another baseboard floor heater when  a $12 heater is perfect.  Kudos to the designer for a great product !!Ol George', 'I wanted this for a very small seedling starter greenhouse but will be unable to use it as it shuts off after 12 hours.  Also when you turn it back on it starts at 90 degrees.  You have to reset the temp and timer every time you turn it back on.  I also bought one for my daughter to use in her tack room for two barn cats but she is also disappointed because of the 12 hour turn off feature.  Only useful if you are there to turn it back on and reset every 12 hours.', 'While this thinks key feature is size, It works well.  Unfortunately the the other plug in a two receptacle outlet cannot be used while this is plugged in.  It blocks the free receptacle partially enough to render it non-usable. It does produce some small fast heat to a rathed general localized area. Is it worth $20.00?  Yes if you will use often, no if you dont require the convenience of it.  Cheaper and more effective heaters are available, its really based on the buyers preference and intended use.  Works great for heating up bathroom when done with showering.  I would reccomend this if you find yourself seeing it  be applicable in a scenario.  ', 'This is a great heater for a small area.I plan on using it for a walk in closet that seems to not get heated very well.I can turn this little guy on for five minutes or so and the problem is solved', 'Better than i expected because the plug works both ways into the outlet, this is good 4 me cause all my outlets are upside down & heater has timer , & low & high..  compact & small, low price i really thinks thats great.  Thx.', 'I love the fact that these heaters have a ground connection.  The third pole helps stabilize the heater in the socket and keeps it from leaning and possibly falling out, like the socket heaters with only two poles.  They are great for a small room like a bathroom. ', "It is very small but it put out some nice heat for it's size.  I like the thermostat feature so it goes off when it gets to that temperature.  ", 'Iâ€™ve given 5 of these as gifts. They are perfect for a bathroom or office or reading area. They are powerful but only heat a small area. Buy using it in the morning by my chair while I read the paper or file paperwork I do not have to turn up my furnace. I can pre heat a bathroom when itâ€™s below zero outside and avoid freezing the second I step out of the shower!Not intended to warm large rooms. ']
